article.headline: Cleveland St. 74, Wright St. 72
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio -- Aaron Pogue led all five Cleveland State starters in double figures with 18 points as the Vikings defeated Wright State 74-72 on Wednesday night. Trevon Harmon and Norris Cole each added 16 points, Jeremy Montgomery had 14 and Tim Kamczyc 10 for the Vikings (23-5, 12-4 Horizon League), who had all five starters play at least 29 minutes. Cole, who finished with 10 assists, and Harmon each played 40 minutes. Cleveland State trailed 66-65 after a 3-pointer from N'Gai Evans with 1:28 left to play. Harmon answered with a 3 on the ensuing possession. Cole and Montgomery combined to go 6 of 6 from the free-throw line in the final 19 seconds to seal the win. Evans and Vaughn Duggins each scored 21 points for the Raiders (17-12, 10-7), who shot 51.1 percent from the floor (23 of 45), including 50 percent from beyond the arc (10 of 20).
